{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_xkxpeuzg3f94_1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both prompts are written and pass self-audit. Here is my report.\n\n## Files created\n\n- `/workspace/prompts/1-spec-003-planning-retry-gate.md` — Layer 2 retry gate\n- `/workspace/prompts/2-spec-003-planning-retry-escalation.md` — Layer 3 exhaustion escalation\n\n## Execution order\n\nSequential (prefixes enforce it). Prompt 2 depends on prompt 1 and contains a fail-loud dependency check: if `grep NewPlanningRetryGate` finds nothing, it must report `status: failed` with `\"planning-retry gate not yet deployed (prompt 1)\"`.\n\n## Key architectural findings (drove the decomposition)\n\n- **Interception point**: result writing flows `NewTaskResultExecutor → writer.WriteResult`. The retry gate is a new `PlanningRetryGate` collaborator invoked in `NewTaskResultExecutor` *before* `WriteResult`, returning `(handled bool, err error)`. This required adding the gate param to `NewTaskResultExecutor` and constructing it in `factory.CreateCommandConsumer` (which already receives `gitClient`, `taskDir`, `currentDateTime` — so prompt 1 needs **no `main.go` change**).\n- **\"Fresh Job spawn\" mechanism resolved**: the controller does not spawn Jobs. Per the agent module's `task-flow-and-failure-semantics.md`, the executor spawns from scanner-published events and dedups on `(repo, sha, task_identifier)` + phase-allowlist. So the retry writes `phase: planning` + a fresh `uuid.NewString()` `task_identifier` into the vault file; the scanner republishes and the executor spawns fresh. I pinned this single mechanism (spec DB 2e left it open).\n- **Failure marker resolved**: verified against `result_writer_test.go` — the marker is `Status: failed` in the `Content` body, not frontmatter status.\n- **Routing key resolved**: `lib.TaskFrontmatter.TaskType() == lib.TaskTypePRReview` (`\"pr-review\"`), with assignee `\"pr-reviewer-agent\"` as documented fallback.\n- **Idempotency**: enforced inside the `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPush` modify closure (git-lock re-read compares on-disk counter to the captured pre-bump value); I rewrote step 4e to state only this one mechanism after the first draft wandered through discarded approaches.\n\n## Open questions surfaced (non-interactive — embedded as comments in prompt 2)\n\nTwo spec Assumptions had no backing in the codebase (grep-verified). Prompt 2 resolves both conservatively and instructs the executor to flag them in `## Improvements`:\n1. **No PR-metadata frontmatter fields exist.** Prompt 2 defines `pr_url` (preferred) or `repository` + `pull_request_number`; missing → skip COMMENT + WARN (matches spec Failure Mode).\n2. **No GitHub token surface exists.** Prompt 2 adds an optional `GITHUB_TOKEN` env var; empty → skip COMMENT + WARN, escalation still lands. No `go-github` dep added (stdlib `net/http`).\n\n## Constraints repeated in each prompt\n\nFrozen constant `maxControllerPlanningRetries = 3` (no knob), frozen `retry N/3:` progress format, frozen `planning_retry_count` field, single-label metric only, strict pr-review+planning+failure gating, no backoff, `bborbe/errors` wrapping, funlen/nestif limits, git-rest as sole write path, no E2E scenario, no commit. Prompt 2 adds: frozen COMMENT template, `COMMENT` event only, `human_review` via `result.ClearAssigneeIfHumanReview` chokepoint, best-effort comment never blocking escalation.\n\n## Docs referenced (in-container paths)\n\nBoth: `go-patterns.md`, `go-error-wrapping-guide.md`, `go-testing-guide.md`, `go-factory-pattern.md`, `go-prometheus-metrics-guide.md`. Prompt 1 also `go-time-injection.md`, `go-cqrs.md`. Prompt 2 also `go-composition.md`, `go-http-service-guide.md`, `go-security-linting.md`.\n\n## Scenario decision\n\nNo scenario prompt — spec explicitly states \"NO new E2E scenario; all behavior reachable via Ginkgo unit tests with mock GitClient and mock PRCommenter.\" Honored.\n\nSuggest running `/audit-prompt /workspace/prompts/1-spec-003-planning-retry-gate.md` and `/audit-prompt /workspace/prompts/2-spec-003-planning-retry-escalation.md` before approving."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aafda89ec99d4af46 (use SendMessage with to: 'aafda89ec99d4af46' to continue this agent)\n<usage>subagent_tokens: 155660\ntool_uses: 43\nduration_ms: 616627</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"538dadd3-1411-457f-8798-0759f57847fd","uuid":"bf86aae9-9440-4d7d-b5bd-d7bf40180529","timestamp":"2026-07-01T12:19:11.168Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Create dark-factory prompt files from the approved spec at `/workspace/specs/in-progress/003-pr-reviewer-plan-recover.md`.\n\nOutput directory: `/workspace/prompts/` (inbox — not `prompts/in-progress/`, dark-factory moves files on approve).\n\nMode: **non-interactive** (daemon-triggered). Do NOT call `AskUserQuestion`. Any ambiguity must be resolved from the spec content alone — surface open questions as comments inside the generated prompts.\n\nThe agent has full access to `/workspace/` for reading source files to verify signatures, look up library APIs, and discover existing patterns. It MUST do so before writing requirements.\n\nThe spec is a 2-prompt decomposition:\n- Prompt 1: Layer 2 retry logic (counter, ## Progress append, phase reset, fresh-task-id requeue, metric counter)\n- Prompt 2: Layer 3 GitHub COMMENT + phase: human_review escalation (depends on prompt 1)\n\nMulti-prompt output uses `1-`, `2-` filename prefixes for execution order.\n\nRead the spec fully before writing any prompts. Follow the agent's workflow and Sizing Guide.","agentId":"aafda89ec99d4af46","agentType":"dark-factory:prompt-creator","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both prompts are written and pass self-audit. Here is my report.\n\n## Files created\n\n- `/workspace/prompts/1-spec-003-planning-retry-gate.md` — Layer 2 retry gate\n- `/workspace/prompts/2-spec-003-planning-retry-escalation.md` — Layer 3 exhaustion escalation\n\n## Execution order\n\nSequential (prefixes enforce it). Prompt 2 depends on prompt 1 and contains a fail-loud dependency check: if `grep NewPlanningRetryGate` finds nothing, it must report `status: failed` with `\"planning-retry gate not yet deployed (prompt 1)\"`.\n\n## Key architectural findings (drove the decomposition)\n\n- **Interception point**: result writing flows `NewTaskResultExecutor → writer.WriteResult`. The retry gate is a new `PlanningRetryGate` collaborator invoked in `NewTaskResultExecutor` *before* `WriteResult`, returning `(handled bool, err error)`. This required adding the gate param to `NewTaskResultExecutor` and constructing it in `factory.CreateCommandConsumer` (which already receives `gitClient`, `taskDir`, `currentDateTime` — so prompt 1 needs **no `main.go` change**).\n- **\"Fresh Job spawn\" mechanism resolved**: the controller does not spawn Jobs. Per the agent module's `task-flow-and-failure-semantics.md`, the executor spawns from scanner-published events and dedups on `(repo, sha, task_identifier)` + phase-allowlist. So the retry writes `phase: planning` + a fresh `uuid.NewString()` `task_identifier` into the vault file; the scanner republishes and the executor spawns fresh. I pinned this single mechanism (spec DB 2e left it open).\n- **Failure marker resolved**: verified against `result_writer_test.go` — the marker is `Status: failed` in the `Content` body, not frontmatter status.\n- **Routing key resolved**: `lib.TaskFrontmatter.TaskType() == lib.TaskTypePRReview` (`\"pr-review\"`), with assignee `\"pr-reviewer-agent\"` as documented fallback.\n- **Idempotency**: enforced inside the `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPush` modify closure (git-lock re-read compares on-disk counter to the captured pre-bump value); I rewrote step 4e to state only this one mechanism after the first draft wandered through discarded approaches.\n\n## Open questions surfaced (non-interactive — embedded as comments in prompt 2)\n\nTwo spec Assumptions had no backing in the codebase (grep-verified). Prompt 2 resolves both conservatively and instructs the executor to flag them in `## Improvements`:\n1. **No PR-metadata frontmatter fields exist.** Prompt 2 defines `pr_url` (preferred) or `repository` + `pull_request_number`; missing → skip COMMENT + WARN (matches spec Failure Mode).\n2. **No GitHub token surface exists.** Prompt 2 adds an optional `GITHUB_TOKEN` env var; empty → skip COMMENT + WARN, escalation still lands. No `go-github` dep added (stdlib `net/http`).\n\n## Constraints repeated in each prompt\n\nFrozen constant `maxControllerPlanningRetries = 3` (no knob), frozen `retry N/3:` progress format, frozen `planning_retry_count` field, single-label metric only, strict pr-review+planning+failure gating, no backoff, `bborbe/errors` wrapping, funlen/nestif limits, git-rest as sole write path, no E2E scenario, no commit. Prompt 2 adds: frozen COMMENT template, `COMMENT` event only, `human_review` via `result.ClearAssigneeIfHumanReview` chokepoint, best-effort comment never blocking escalation.\n\n## Docs referenced (in-container paths)\n\nBoth: `go-patterns.md`, `go-error-wrapping-guide.md`, `go-testing-guide.md`, `go-factory-pattern.md`, `go-prometheus-metrics-guide.md`. Prompt 1 also `go-time-injection.md`, `go-cqrs.md`. Prompt 2 also `go-composition.md`, `go-http-service-guide.md`, `go-security-linting.md`.\n\n## Scenario decision\n\nNo scenario prompt — spec explicitly states \"NO new E2E scenario; all behavior reachable via Ginkgo unit tests with mock GitClient and mock PRCommenter.\" Honored.\n\nSuggest running `/audit-prompt /workspace/prompts/1-spec-003-planning-retry-gate.md` and `/audit-prompt /workspace/prompts/2-spec-003-planning-retry-escalation.md` before approving."}],"totalDurationMs":616627,"totalTokens":155660,"totalToolUseCount":43,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":548,"cache_read_input_tokens":153462,"output_tokens":1648,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_reques